com/photo/131082550.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Spirit Airlines has ceased operations after decades of making air travel affordable. TikTok founder Hunter Peterson has launched a movement to "nationalise" the airline with collective ownership. This initiative, inspired by the Green Bay Packers model, aims to shift focus from profit to service. Millions have pledged support, showing a growing trend in crowd-equity perception.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/tiktok-crowdfunding-push-to-purchase-spirit-airlines-hits-335-million/articleshow/131082550.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/tiktok-crowdfunding-push-to-purchase-spirit-airlines-hits-335-million/articleshow/131082550.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-14T17:45:00+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131082588,imgsize-1071699.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[US Firm Revamps Bran Castle: Ad Populum takes 80% stake; aims to boost global tourism]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131083558.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Bran Castle, the inspiration for Dracula, is entering a new era of international tourism under American ownership. U.S. businessman Joel Weinshanker's Ad Populum, which manages Graceland, has acquired an 80% stake, aiming to boost visitor numbers from the US and Western Europe. This move blends pop culture with historical preservation, ensuring the castle's financial viability and continued allure.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/the-real-dracula-castle-just-got-a-powerful-new-owner-from-the-united-states/articleshow/131083558.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/the-real-dracula-castle-just-got-a-powerful-new-owner-f